synopses.synopsis: 21st Precinct. It's just lines on a map of the city of New York. Most of the 173,000 people wedged into the nine-tenths of a square mile between Fifth Avenue and the East River wouldn't know, if you asked them, that they lived or worked in the 21st. Whether they know it or not, the security of their persons, their homes, and their property is the job of the men of the 21st.' - That was the opening to every show; a show about the 21st police precinct in New York City. While shows like Dragnet focused on police work and behind-the-scenes details, this show did the same but seemed far more legitimate. The show had no music so moments of fear, horror, sadness were all caught with a kind of naked realism.
